    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-07-27T09:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-07-27T09:00:00-05:00" n="826"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d826">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">892.014/7–2746: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Siam</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stanton</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <gloss target="#t_Niact1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">niact</hi>
                        </gloss>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-07-27T10:00:00-04:00"
                            >July 27, 1946—10 a.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>632. Inform <gloss target="#t_FonOff1">FonOff</gloss> urgently French have
                    informed us<note n="40" xml:id="d826fn1">On July 26.</note> they will very
                    shortly seek US good offices present and urge Siamese acceptance proposals for
                    solution disputed areas problem within UN framework. Details follow soonest but
                    possibly few days delay. <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss> generally
                    familiar French proposals and considers them so important it urges Siamese Govt
                    consider them and instruct delegation prior its departure delaying departure if
                    need be. Agreement reached here Siamese complaint will not be placed on
                    provisional agenda <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss> until Siamese delegation
                    arrives. Short delay will therefore not prejudice Siamese position.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Byrnes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
